Karl wrote:

>In the morning, when the engine is cold, look at the crossbar where the cable attaches. It the 'arm' standing up? Can you push the arm forward or is it all the way forward when cold?
>
>All the way forward means the thermostat is pulling the flaps to the closed position or the flaps/thermostat is mis-adjusted.
>
>Standing up means the thermostat is open, warm, or blown.
>
